<body>
    <h1>Welcome to Rajkot</h1>
    <p>Rajkot is the fourth-largest city in the state of Gujarat, India. Situated on the banks of the Aji River and Nyari River, it is known for its history, culture, and industry.</p>
    
    
    <div class="info-section">
        <h2>Key Facts</h2>
        <p><strong>Location:</strong> Gujarat, India</p>
        <p><strong>Population:</strong> Approx. 1.8 million (2023)</p>
        <p><strong>Known For:</strong> Ghee, Engineering, Jewelry, and as a former princely state capital.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="info-section">
        <h2>Major Landmarks</h2>
        <ul class="landmarks-list">
            <li><strong>Kaba Gandhi No Delo:</strong> The childhood home of Mahatma Gandhi, now a memorial museum.</li>
            <li><strong>Watson Museum:</strong> One of the oldest museums in Gujarat, located in Jubilee Garden.</li>
            <li><strong>Lal Pari Lake:</strong> A popular picnic and bird-watching spot on the outskirts of the city.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
